eith Nkrumah]]\n|13 April 2013\n|Norfolk State University Relays\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Norfolk, Virginia|Norfolk]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=110m Hurdles Result|url=http://www.tfrrs.org/results/28689_1877019.html?athlete_hnd=2214434|work=tfrrs.org|date=13 April 2013|accessdate=26 November 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[400 metres hurdles|400 m hurdles]]\n|50.40\n|[[Keith Nkrumah]]\n|5 May 2012\n|MEAC Championships\n|[[Greensboro, North Carolina|Greensboro]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=400m Hurdles Result|url=https://www.tfrrs.org/results/26106/1650733/MEAC_Outdoor_Track_&_Field_Championships/400H/|work=tfrrs.org|date=5 May 2012|accessdate=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[3000 metres steeplechase|3000 m steeplechase]]\n|8:57.54\n|[[Robert Hackman]]\n|1 September 1972\n|[[Athletics at the 1972 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]\n|{{flagicon|FRG}} [[Munich]], West Germany\n|\n|-\n|[[High jump]]\n|2.24 m\n|[[Kwaku Boateng (athlete)|Kwaku Boateng]]\n|8 August 1996\n|\n|{{flagicon|CAN}} [[Kitchener, Ontario|Kitchener]], Canada\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Pole vault]]\n|rowspan=2|5.40 m\n|rowspan=2|[[Jordan Yamoah]]\n|25 May 2013\n|[[NCAA Men's Division II Outdoor Track and Field Championships|NCAA Division II Championships]]\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Pueblo, Colorado|Pueblo]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Pole Vault Results|url=https://www.tfrrs.org/results/31154_1944585.html?athlete_hnd=3717635|publisher=tfrrs.org|date=25 May 2013|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|9 April 2016\n|ASU David Noble Relays\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[San Angelo]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Pole Vault Results|url=https://www.tfrrs.org/results/43763_2783073.html?athlete_hnd=3717635|publisher=tfrrs.org|date=9 April 2016|accessdate=13 September 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Long jump]]\n|8.43 m <small>(-0.2&nbsp;m/s)</small>\n|[[Ignisious Gaisah]]\n|14 July 2006\n|[[Golden Gala]]\n|{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Rome]], Italy\n|\n|-\n|[[Triple jump]]\n|17.23 m <small>(-0.5&nbsp;m/s)</small>\n|[[Andrew Owusu]]\n|19 August 1998\n|[[1998 African Championships in Athletics|African Championships]]\n|{{flagicon|SEN}} [[Dakar]], Senegal\n|\n|-\n|[[Shot put]]\n|17.97 m\n|[[Kwabena Keene]]\n|20 April 2012\n|ACC Championships\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Charlottesville, Virginia|Charlottesville]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Shot Put Results|url=http://www.directathletics.com/results/track/24668_1614990.html?athlete_hnd=2231745|publisher=directathletics.com|date=20 April 2012|accessdate=8 November 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Discus throw]]\n|52.98 m\n|[[Kwabena Keene]]\n|15 April 2010\n|ACC Championships\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Clemson, South Carolina|Clemson]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Discus Throw Results|url=http://www.directathletics.com/results/track/14514_1074477.html?athlete_hnd=2231745|publisher=directathletics.com|date=15 April 2010|accessdate=17 October 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Hammer throw]]\n|50.56 m\n|[[David Dadzie]]\n|20 May 2016\n|Great Lakes Elite Meet\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Ohio Wesleyan University|Ohio]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite news|title=Calvin's David Dadzie breaks Ghana national record in hammer throw|url=http://www.mlive.com/smallcolleges/grandrapids/index.ssf/2016/05/calvins_david_dadzie_breaks_gh.html|publisher=mlive.com|date=20 May 2016|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Javelin throw]]\n|83.09 m\n|[[John Ampomah]]\n|8 July 2016\n|Soga-Nana Memorial\n|{{flagicon|GHA}} [[Cape Coast]], Ghana\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Soga-Nana Memorial, Cape Coast (Ghana) 8/07/2016|url=http://www.africathle.com/2016/07/08/soga-nana-memorial-cape-coast-ghana-8072016/|publisher=africathle.com|date=8 July 2016|accessdate=12 July 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[Decathlon]]\n|7811 pts\n|[[Atsu Nyamadi]]\n|21\u201322 April 2017\n|Virginia Challenge\n|{{flagicon|USA}} [[Charlottesville, Virginia|Charlottesville]], United States\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Decathlon Results|url=https://www.directathletics.com/results/track/51364_3144826.html?athlete_hnd=5612456|work=d